#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*\tOpen the configuration dialog for this addon from the NVDA tools menu or from the settings panel According to your version of NVDA;\n"
"\t*\tIn the Clock setup dialog, the first two Combo Box controls allow you to choose your prefered time and date display formats;\n"
"\t*\tThe Combo Box control labeled \"Interval\" allows you to set the interval for automatic time announcement (Every 10 minutes, Every 15 minutes, Every 30 minutes, Every hour, or Off);\n"
"\t*\tThe Combo Box control labeled \"Time announcement\" (only visible if the choice \"off\" is not selected in the interval Combo Box) lets you configure how the automatic time announcement should be reported (Speech and sound, Speech only, or Sound only) when automatic time announcement is working;\n"
"\t*\tThe Combo box control labeled \"Clock chime sound\" (only visible if the choice \"off\" is not selected in the interval Combo Box) lets you choose between various clock sounds that will be played when automatic time announcement is working and reported with sound;\n"
"\t*\tThe Checkbox control labeled \"Quiet hours\" (only visible if the choice \"off\" is not selected in the interval Combo Box) lets you configure time range when automatic time announcement shouldn't occure;\n"
"\t*\tThe Checkbox control labeled \"input in 24-hour format\" (only visible if quiet hours are enabled) allows you to configure wether you want to input time for quiet hours in 12-hour (A.M. or P.M.), or european 24-hour format;\n"
"\t*\tThe Edit box controls for start and end time (only visible if quiet hours are enabled) let you configure time range for quiet hours. The time should be entered in HH:MM format if the \"input in 24-hour format\" checkbox is checked, otherwise you must use a 12 hour format as described below;\n"
"\t*\tWhen done, tab to the OK button and activate it by pressing Enter to save your settings;\n"
"\t*\tIn the Alarm setup dialog, the first Combo Box control allow you to choose your prefered countdown timer before the alarm ring;\n"
"\t*\tThe Edit box control lets you type your time waiting before the alarm ring. This duration must be specified in 1 or more digits, not a decimal number;\n"
"\t*\tThe Combo box control labeled \"Alarm sound\" lets you choose between various alarm sounds that will be played when the alarm time arrives;\n"
"\t*\tThe pause button allows you to pause/resume too long alarms;\n"
"\t*\tThe stop button allows you to stop too long alarms;\n"
"\t*\tWhen done, tab to the OK button and activate it by pressing Enter. A message should be displayed to remind you of the waiting time before the alarm;\n"
"*\tPress NVDA+F12 once to get current time, twice to get current date, or thrice to get the current day, week number, as well as the remaining days before the end of the current year.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Key commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"- NVDA+F12, get current time; - NVDA+F12 pressed twice quickly, get current "
"date; - NVDA+F12 pressed thrice quickly, reports the current day, the week "
"number, the current year and the remaining days before the end of the year."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"- There is a script that gives the remaining and elapsed time before the "
"next alarm; - There is no keyboard gesture assigned to this script, you will "
"have to do it yourself in the \"Input gestures\" dialog box, in the \"Clock"
"\" category; - This gesture pressed twice quickly, cancel the next alarm; - "
"There is another script to stop the sound that is currently playing, its "
"gesture is also not defined; - That script can also be called using the "
"clock layer commands described below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Layered commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To use layered commands, press NVDA+Shift+F12 followed by one of the "
"following keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"- S: Starts, resets or stops the stopwatch; - R: Resets stopwatch to 0 "
"without restarting it; - A: gives the remaining and elapsed time before the "
"next alarm; - C: Cancel the next alarm; - Space: Speaks current stopwatch or "
"count-down timer; - p: If an alarm is too long, allows to stop it; - H: List "
"all layered commands (Help)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Syntax to use for quiet hours"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"- To avoid bugs, the quiet hours must follow a rigorous and precise syntax; "
"- If you check the \"Input in 24-hour format\" checkbox, the format must be "
"\"HH:MM\"; - If you uncheck the \"Input in 24-hour format\" checkbox, the "
"format must be \"HH:MM AM\" or \"HH:MM PM\", the HH must contain a 12-hour "
"format, from 0 to 12 and the \"AM\"|\"PM\" suffix can be in lowercase or "
"uppercase - If you check the Quiet hours\" checkbox and keep the \"Quiet "
"hours start time\" or \"Quiet hours end time\" field empty, or type a "
"mistaken value, the \"Quiet hours\" checkbox will be unchecked "
"automatically, to avoid errors; - A message should be displayed to report "
"your error."
msgstr ""

